content: Another interesting example is to interpolate colours. Now, this one is a bit tricky for one reason which is: Animated cannot animate some style properties with native driven animations. This means that if you animate a backgroundColor property using the native driver, you should get an error saying that some properties cannot be animated this way. Since backgroundColor won’t be animated using the native driver, let’s keep this in mind when writing the code. In this case, all you need is to set useNativeDriver to false, which might slow down your animations on low-end devices.
